          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "UNFLD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " measurements of electrodisintegration cross",
                "sections, (e,p) and (e,2p), and their corresponding",
                "electrodis-integration-plus-photodisintegration yields",
                "for 29Si and 30Si are presented. The experiment covers",
                "the range from 20 to 60 MeV electron incident energies.",
                "the experimental results were analyzed using e1 and e2",
                "distorted-wave born approximation virtual photon",
                "spectra for a finite nucleous in order to obtain the",
                "corresponding photodisintegration cross sections for",
                "both channels and isotopes. For 29Si the integrated",
                " (g,p)cross sections is 47% bigger than (g,n) while",
                "for 30Si they are of same order of magnitude. For both",
                "isotopes the (g,p) channel is dominantly e1. The (g,2p)",
                "channel is much smaller than the (g,2n) channel but",
                "the e2 contribution to this decay mode is of the same",
                "magnitude of e1."
              ]
            }
          ],
